          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱός</span></b> , gen. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱοῦ, υἷος, υἱέος</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱῷ, υἷι, υἱέι</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱόν, υἷα,
            υἱέα</span>, du. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἷε</span>, pl.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἷες, υἱέες</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱοῖσι, υἱάσι</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἷας, υἱέας, υἱεῖς</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">son;</span> freq. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἷες Ἀχαιῶν</span> for <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἀχαιοί</span>. The diphthong is sometimes shortened in <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱός, υἱόν, υἱέ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 11.270</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            478</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          4.473</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
